package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"os"

	wav "github.com/youpy/go-wav"
)

func main() {
	err := run()
	if err != nil {
		panic(err)
	}
}

func run() (err error) {
	f, err := os.Open("rach.wav")
	if err != nil {
		return
	}
	defer f.Close()

	reader := wav.NewReader(f)
	fm, err := reader.Format()
	if err != nil {
		return
	}
	fmt.Printf("fm: %+v", fm)
	start := uint32(48000 * 10)
	end := uint32(start + 48000*3)
	_, err = reader.ReadSamples(start)
	if err != nil {
		return
	}
	fmt.Println(end)

	outfile, err := os.Create("rach2.wav")
	if err != nil {
		return
	}
	defer outfile.Close()

	writer := wav.NewWriter(outfile, end-start, fm.NumChannels, fm.SampleRate, fm.BitsPerSample)
	samples, err := reader.ReadSamples(end - start)
	if err != nil {
		return
	}
	err = writer.WriteSamples(samples)
	if err != nil {
		return
	}

	return
}
